item.title: Erin Dahl
item.description: Erin Dahl joined the Karstens Lab in January 2020 as a DIMCE Intern. She continued working in the Karstens Lab as a student worker on improving data visualization and generalizing code workflows. Erin has recently completed her Bioinformatics degree at Pacific University (January 21') and is now a Research Assistant.

item.title: Emory Neer
item.description:
Emory Neer studies public health and geographic information systems at Portland State. She has worked in the Karstens Lab as a part of the Build EXITO program on creating a universially colorblind friendly palette.

https://www.pdx.edu/exito/
